The paper deals with the problem of searching people in an unconstrained environment using natural language descriptions, which involves computer vision, natural language processing, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper also deals with natural language descriptions. The paper also involves robotics, which suggests the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm that adapts models for visual and language understanding, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper introduces a greedy algorithm to rank questions, which involves machine learning and falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
